cs.SD, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.CL

Reasoning: 
- cs.SD (Sound): The paper deals with audio signals and their classification, making this sub-category the most likely.
- cs.SI (Speech and Signal Processing): The paper focuses on audio denoising and speech enhancement, which are both signal processing tasks.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a modified dictionary learning algorithm, which falls under the umbrella of machine learning.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper discusses the effectiveness of the proposed method as a stand-alone solution, which can be seen as a control system.
- cs.CL (Computation and Language): The paper involves natural language processing techniques for audio classification, which can be considered a sub-field of computational linguistics.
